Package com.shortcuts.table

Class Table

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.shortcuts.table.Table
  • public class Table
extends java.lang.Object
    Table class is used as a data structure. It's kinda of plain database with CRUD functionality. It allows you to store, add, insert, etc. rows and columns. Each Table instance has table title, description and two-dimensional data array. Also, you can print out each table in a good-looking form. Type of a column is defined when you add the first row, so the sequential types will be defined as a previous ones.

      • Table

        public Table​(java.lang.String tableTitle,
             java.lang.String description,
             java.lang.String[] titles)
        Constructs a new Table instance, receives a title(tableTitle) and description of a table and an array of column titles as String objects. The initial capacity of data array 15 by 15, next size will increase or decrease, according to adding or removing rows or columns.
        Parameters:
        tableTitle - is a title of new table
        description - is a short description of a table
        titles - is an array of columns titles, also it's defined an initial number of columns
